article.headline: Winn scores 17, Walker adds 12 as No. 21 Pitt dumps Arizona
article.linkText: Winn, Walker power No. 21 Pitt to win vs. Arizona
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) --  Mallorie Winn scored 17 points and Marcedes Walker added 12 points and 11 rebounds to lead Pittsburgh (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today; No. 20 AP) to an 81-58 victory over Arizona on Saturday in the WBCA Classic.

Winn, sidelined all of last season by a knee injury, had five 3-pointers. Jania Sims also had 12 points and Taneisha Harrison added 11.

Pittsburgh (2-0) used two 15-0 runs in the first half to take a 40-15 lead.

Ashley Whisonant scored 19 points and Amina Njonkou had 14 for Arizona (0-2), which hasn't started a season with two losses since 1994-95. The Wildcats shot only 32.3 percent from the field.

On Sunday, Pitt will face Penn State, and Arizona will meet Charlotte.
